    "slug": "intense-winds-weather",
    "description": "<p><strong>Intense Winds</strong> are, for many, completely unmanageable. Without decent aerodynamics, you'd basically be helpless. But for the lords of the air, they might as well be unassailable in their \"gale-force fortress\".</p><p><strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Effects:</span></strong></p><ul><li>For the purposes of Abilities, Attacks, Perks, and Traits, this Weather is considered to also be “Windy”.</li><li>Flying-Type creatures and creatures in the Flying Movement State have their SPD increased 60%.</li><li>[Wind] attacks deal 80% more damage.</li><li>All creatures with a Flight Movement Score have that Score increase by 60%.</li><li>Flying-Type creatures gain a Flight Score equal to 80% of their Overland (minimum 3).</li><li>Flying-Type creatures have their DEF stat increased by 25% and SPDEF stat increased by 25%.</li><li>The Flying Type’s weaknesses are instead neutral.</li><li>All [Dash] and [Reckless] attacks without [Push X] gain [Push 1]. When Pushed, all creatures are Pushed an additional X meters (minimum of 0), where X is equal to 12 minus their Weight Class.</li></ul>"
  },
